    • name

      public javafx.beans.property.ReadOnlyStringProperty nameProperty

      Returns the property containing the name of this UIBook.

      1. The name is only used for UI purposes, such as being displayed in a tooltip upon a user hovering over the button for this UIBook.
      2. To change the actual button for this UIBook, see buttonIDProperty().

  • Constructor Details

    • UIBook

      public UIBook​(net.rgielen.fxweaver.core.FxWeaver weaver, org.springframework.context.ConfigurableApplicationContext ctx, String name, String buttonID, Function<UIBook,​UIPage<?>> coverPageFunction, Runnable onAction)

    • UIBook

      public UIBook​(net.rgielen.fxweaver.core.FxWeaver weaver, org.springframework.context.ConfigurableApplicationContext ctx, String name, String buttonID, Function<UIBook,​UIPage<?>> coverPageFunction, Runnable onAction, javafx.scene.layout.StackPane contentPane)

      Fully parameterized constructor for UIBook objects.


      Parameters:
      weaver - The FxWeaver instance to be used for linking UIBook JavaFX attributes to Spring.
      • See Springable.weaver()
      ctx - The ApplicationContext that allows easy access to Spring-related functionality for this UIBook.
      • See Springable.ctx()
      name - The name to be assigned to this UIBook.
      • See nameProperty()
      buttonID - The ID mapped to the cached image to be used as the button for this UIBook.

      coverPageFunction - The Function that will retrieve the UIPage to be used as the cover page of this UIBook.
      • If the specified Function is null, a FallbackPage will be used as the cover page instead.
      onAction - A Runnable that will be executed when the button for this UIBook is pressed.
      • See ImageButton.initialize() for exact implementation.
      contentPane - The StackPane in which the contents (pages) of this UIBook are displayed.
      • Accessed via getContent().getDisplayContainer()

    • getUIDProcessor

      public UIDProcessor getUIDProcessor()
      Description copied from interface: UIDProcessable

      Returns the UIDProcessor instance for this UIDProcessable object.


      Example Implementation

      private UIDProcessor uIDContainer;

 //...

 @Override
 public UIDProcessor getUIDProcessor()
 {
     if (uIDContainer == null) // Lazy Initialization
         uIDContainer = new UIDProcessor("group-name");
     return uIDContainer;
 }

      Details

      1. In most cases, it is recommended that UIDProcessor objects are stored as lazy-initialized singleton field variables as shown in the example above.
